      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 527,
      "message": "If there's nothing to do if portNodeTemplateId is blank, then just return it, no need to proceed. This makes the code much easier to follow - condition not met -> stop right there. This is sometimes called \"guard clauses\" (see for example, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guard_(computer_science) and https://refactoring.com/catalog/replaceNestedConditionalWithGuardClauses.html)\n\nAlso, is it OK for it to be blank? If not, that may point at a problem in the calling code and an exception should be thrown, not just nothing be done silently.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2017-11-03 12:58:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
