      "message": "This code calls StringBuilder.toString() twice, one time just to calculate its length. First, StingBuilder has a lenth() method. Second, it would be better to manipulate the instance of StringBuilder itself, for example using it substring() or deleteCharAt(). That is without converting it to String first.\n\nExample:\nsb.substring(0, sb.lenght() - 1).toString();",
